[SN]TITLE[SN]
Drugs charge after men found unconscious in Belfast

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 33-year-old man has been charged with drugs offences after an incident involving three men who were found unconscious in Belfast City Centre.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The three were found on Saturday night just before 21:00 GMT on Donegall Pass.
One of them was initially described as critically ill but all three have since been released from hospital.
The man has been charged with possession of a class A drug and possession of a class A drug with intent to supply.
He will appear at Belfast Magistrates Court on 6 January.
